Reasoning: The dominant remaining errors are task OMISSION and HALLUCINATION caused by an unclear boundary around what counts as a task when work is mentioned as descriptive progress versus a maintained work item. Existing rules cover task/decision boundaries and status mapping, but they do not explicitly tell the model to keep only durable work items and exclude incidental substeps or demo-prep details, which explains the missing "Design feedback loop" and extra one-off tasks. I chose ADD because this concern is not directly covered by any current rule, and I rejected rewording the decision rule since prior attempts on that theme were already discarded and the main misses are now in task inclusion criteria.

